NEWSWEEK CHAMPIONS CUP
March 10, 1995
Marcelo Rios
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
 Q.   Can you describe the injury, please?

 M. RIOS:  Well, I was talking with the doctors like distention,
I don't know how to say it in English, but it hurt when I my play
my backhand, it is hard to move.

 JOE LYNCH:  Left hip area.

 Q.   Is it a muscle type of injury?

 M. RIOS:  I don't know.

 Q.   Did you suffer yesterday?

 M. RIOS:  No, I had it before like in Memphis, I stopped like
one week, then like I was okay and it happened here.

 Q.   After Memphis, did you play at all or did you take time
off?

 M. RIOS:  Yeah, I take time off.

 Q.   Is that the plan now?

 M. RIOS:  I don't know.  I have to play next week Lipton and
I don't know how I will feel.  I will take couple of days; see
what is going to happen.

 Q.   This was the first time you had the problem Memphis?


 M. RIOS:  Yeah.  First time.

 Q.   Not in the juniors or anything?

 M. RIOS:  No, never.

 Q.   Before the injury, how do you think you were playing
today?

 M. RIOS:  Well, I have been playing good this week.  I was not
playing very good, but, well, one more match like this, hard court
playing tennis, you have a lot of leg injuries.  One injury, I
have to fix it up and go to the other tournament.

 Q.   This is your first time playing Boris?

 M. RIOS:  Yeah, first time.

 Q.   What were your impressions of his game?

 M. RIOS:  Well, he has a good serve and good volley and from
baseline he is -- well, when we play points from baseline, I win,
but from like serve and volley, he is great.

